{{Infobox lake | name = Tianping Reservoir | native_name = 青山湖 | native_name_lang = zh-hans | other_name = Qingshan Lake | image = Tianping Reservoir 106.jpg | alt = | caption = Tianping Reservoir | image_bathymetry = | alt_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Qingshanqiao Town, Ningxiang|Qingshanqiao Town]], [[Ningxiang]], [[Hunan]] | coords = {{coord|27.990|111.998|type:waterbody_region:CN|format=dms|display =inline,title}} | type = [[reservoir (water)|Reservoir]] | inflow = | outflow = [[Wei River (Xiang River)|Wei River]] | catchment = | basin_countries = [[People's Republic of China|China]] | agency = | date-built = 1970s | date-flooded = 1970s | length = | width = | area = {{convert|4.2|km2|acre}} | depth = | max-depth = | volume = {{convert|44160,000|m3|e9USgal}} | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | frozen = | islands = | cities = | reference = }}
'''The Tianping Reservoir''' ({{zh|s=田坪水库|t=田坪水庫|p=Tiánpíng Shuǐkù}}) is a large [[reservoir (water)|reservoir]] located in the western part of [[Ningxiang|Ningxiang City]], [[Hunan Province|Hunan]], [[China]]. It is the largest body of water in [[Ningxiang]] and the second largest reservoir in [[Ningxiang]]. The reservoir is the source of the [[Wei River (Xiang River)|Wei River]] ({{lang|zh-hans|沩水河}}).
Created by damming some small rivers, the Tianping Reservoir has an area of {{convert|4.2|km2|acre}} and a capacity of {{convert|4416|m3|e9USgal}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nxqsq.com/news_view.asp?newsid=20|title=《芙蓉山水》|accessdate=2006-04-17|work=|publisher=青山桥人民政府网|language=Chinese|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060702173902/http://www.nxqsq.com/news_view.asp?newsid=20|archivedate=2006-07-02|df=}}</ref>
==History== In the 1970s Yang Shifang ({{lang|zh-hans|杨世芳}}), head of the People's Government of Ningxiang, planned to build a reservoir for [[irrigation]], flood control, [[electricity generation]] and fish farming. Due to poverty, the government mobilized the masses and used a large amount of human resources to complete the build rather than use [[heavy equipment (construction)|heavy construction equipment]].
