The 2001 [[World Solar Challenge]] was one of a biennial series of [[Solar car racing|solar-powered car races]], covering about {{convert|3000|km|mi|abbr=on}} through the Australian [[Outback]], from [[Darwin, Northern Territory|Darwin]], [[Northern Territory]] to [[Adelaide]], [[South Australia]]. The winner was a [[Nuna]] "Alpha Centauri" car built by [[Nuon (company)|Nuon]] of the Netherlands.
